  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='black' class='header'>ITEM COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>I RECOMMEND TAILORING THIS WAY...</font>, By Haroth</b><br><br><p>&nbsp;If you're going to tailor start out with silk thread and swatches, go to patchwork or leather padding, then try combining silk cords and low quality pelts of any kind from the common lands to make pouches, after large bags are trivial (late 40's) start working on cured silk masks. Go to east
Karana and kill crag spiders or buy stacks of silk swatches for near 30 platinum a stack. get a backpack full of silk swatches and run to
East Freeport and start making heady kiolas. bring tons of patterns and start making cured silk masks till trivial (82) then work on tailored quivers.
Don't make handmade backpacks until they're trivial. Once you can make backpacks start raking in the dough to buy hq cat pelts from other players for 5pp each cat pelt. :)</p>
<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>FYI</font>, By Omnisoul</b><br><br><p>&nbsp;This pack is used for a ranger quest for a weight reducing pack in nk... I sold these left and right in nk and sk,
shouldn't keep a supply to meet the demand</p>
<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>HQ BACKPACK WHEN TO TRY</font>, By Whak</b><br><br><p>&nbsp;The HQ bear pelts are difficult to come by so you should hoard them like a misers gold and kill every bear you see if tailoring is to be a good money maker for you.  I started attempting them at a skill level of 70 and would have a 50 percent success rate.  If you can, I would do cured silk
armour instead as much as you can to build skill and earn money.  The spider silks are easier to come by, but you need huge amounts of them.  Most people say EAST Karana is the place to go, but I find West commons is best and you have a good chance of getting some HQ bear pelts as well.  The spiders are lower level and more abundant and it is close to the auction tunnel. If around level 20, crag spiders in EK will give exp and lots of spider silks.  I sell a full set of cured silk for about 150 pp.  It is very much in demand, though the backpacks are still better.  The shaman potion bag is also an excellent skill builder-- 1 silk cord and 1 grizzly pelt.  Not so much in demand anymore, but might sell for 20pp.  Demand for the backpacks has not diminished unlike demand for most other things.  High level questers need one for every slot in their bank.  I try to buy the pelt for 25pp and sell the pack for 100pp.  Also be sure to build your tailoring skill
beyond the trivial level of 88.  You will still have many failures if you stop at 88.  Beyond backpacks, there is much for tailoring unless you get into the cultural items,  but I am not the right race.<br>
</p>
<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>DONE THAT BY LUCK</font>, By Samite</b><br><br>Some one gave me a 10 slot backpack for free, so being greedy I asked where she got it,she said she makes them I said how she said, &#34;HQ bear pelt and backpack patern.&#34;I got them tailored on my skill is areound 50 or less. I guess I got lucky?<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>BACKPACK PATTERN</font>, By Salishan</b><br><br>Backpack patterns can also be found in Misty Thicket.  There is a shop almost directly forward from where you exit Rivervale.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
